name: Jay Leno
monologue: President Obama will begin a three-state bus tour. I believe the three states are confusion, delusion, and desperation.

name: Jay Leno
monologue: The Republicans had their big debate in Iowa. You know who the winner was? Anyone that didn’t watch.

name: Jay Leno
monologue: It’s the 76th anniversary of social security. I mention it because there’s no guarantee that there will be a 77th.

name: Jimmy Fallon
monologue: A new survey revealed that being an IT guy is the most hated job in the country. Or as President Obama put it, “Wanna bet?”

name: Jimmy Fallon
monologue: A new study found that 20 percent of Internet time is spent on social networking sites. While the other 80 percent is spent hiding a Facebook window behind Excel.

name: Jimmy Fallon
monologue: A school in New Zealand discovered that a model skeleton for an anatomy class was actually a real human skeleton. Yeah, they made the realization when they noticed they hadn’t seen their anatomy teacher in about eight months.

name: Jimmy Fallon
monologue: The federal government has a new plan that will let people send texts to 911. Yeah, it’s a little frustrating when you try to text “Burglar! Please hurry!,” and it auto-corrects to “Burger, please. Hungry.”
